Description
!-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
BNMERGE is a tool to merge the output files produced by BFM_NEMO when run
in parallel. 
The output files are remapped from the 1D BFM grid to the 3D NEMO grid.
All variables are copied and the output file contains also the Tmask and
lat lon arrays.

Usage
!-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
bnmerge is controlled by the namelist bnmerge.nml (see bnmerge.nml example)


Compilation
!-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
Change the the Makefile with the name of the included compiler file 
from the Compilers directory. Run gmake.

Script (bnmerge.sh)
!-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-
Script will help to compile and execute the merging of parallel or serial version.
To execute in parallel:
   - export variable PARALLEL equal to yes.
      - EX: export PARALLEL=yes
   - load module pnetcdf (in the shell): module load NETCDF/parallel-netcdf-1.3.1
To execute in serial:
   - leave the variable PARALLEL empty.
      - EX: export PARALLEL=
   - load module netcdf3 (in the shell): module load NETCDF/netcdf-4.2.1.1_netcdf3